Package model

Class Register

java.lang.Object
model.Register
public class Register extends Object
The Register class contains several observable lists and methods for working with them. These lists are used to represent the tables in the database and are used to populate table views and combo boxes within the application.

    • filterDivisionByCountry

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<FirstLevelDivision> filterDivisionByCountry(Country country)
      This method is passed a country object and filters a list of division objects by countryId. It is used to narrow selections in the combo boxes to only the divisions matching the countryID.
      Parameters:
      country - the country to filter by
      Returns:
      matchingDivisions

    • findAvailableEndTimes

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<LocalTime> findAvailableEndTimes(LocalTime start)
      This method is passed a start LocalTime object and filters a list of end LocalTime objects. It is used to narrow selections in the combo boxes for end times that only occur after the selected start time.
      Parameters:
      start - the start time to filter by
      Returns:
      availableEndTimes

    • buildStartTimeList

      public static void buildStartTimeList()
      This method is used to build the list of LocalTime objects for the allStartTimes ObservableList. It builds this list based off of a list of ZonedDateTime objects tied to EST for the business location to handle time conversions within the application.

    • buildEndTimeList

      public static void buildEndTimeList()
      This method is used to build the list of LocalTime objects for the allEndTimes ObservableList. It builds this list based off of a list of ZonedDateTime objects tied to EST for the business location to handle time conversions within the application.
